# Page Navigation Pattern

Methods should return the next page!

## Real World Scenario

Fluent interfaces allow you to write tests like sentences (`login().then(home).then(profile)`). This improves readability and developer experience by providing autocomplete suggestions for available actions on the next page.

## Fluent Navigation

```javascript
class LoginPage {
    async login(email, password) {
        await this.emailInput.fill(email);
        await this.passwordInput.fill(password);
        await this.submitButton.click();
        return new DashboardPage(this.page);
    }
}

// Usage
const dashboard = await loginPage.login('user', 'pass');
await dashboard.doSomething();
```

## Benefits

- Clear flow between pages
- Type safety (with TypeScript)
- Self-documenting tests

## Your Task
1. Login should return HomePage
2. HomePage should have getWelcomeMessage 
3. Chain the calls and return the message

