# Test Data from JSON

Externalize your test data!

## Real World Scenario

Hardcoding test data in code (e.g., specific usernames) is bad practice. Externalizing data to JSON files allows you to manage test scenarios separately from code and easily swap data sets for different environments.

## JSON Data File

```json
// users.json
[
    { "email": "user1@test.com", "name": "User One" },
    { "email": "user2@test.com", "name": "User Two" }
]
```

## Load in Tests

```javascript
const users = require('./users.json');
// or: import users from './users.json';

for (const user of users) {
    await test.step(`Test user: ${user.name}`, async () => {
        // Test with this user's data
    });
}
```

## Your Task
1. Use the provided user data
2. Fill the form for last user
3. Return the greeting

