# Environment-Based Data

Different data for dev/staging/prod!

## Real World Scenario

You can't use detailed production data in a staging environment. Environment-based configuration ensures your tests automatically pick the right URLs, credentials, and API keys for the environment they are running in.

## Config Pattern

```javascript
const config = {
    dev: {
        baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',
        user: { email: 'dev@test.com' }
    },
    staging: {
        baseURL: 'https://staging.example.com',
        user: { email: 'staging@test.com' }
    },
    prod: {
        baseURL: 'https://example.com',
        user: { email: 'prod@test.com' }
    }
};

const env = process.env.TEST_ENV || 'dev';
const { baseURL, user } = config[env];
```

